    "text": "To see that n divides an, factor n as 2km, with m odd. Then note that k ≤ n ≤ n(n − 1)/2, and that there exists i ≤ m − 1 such that m divides 2i − 1, namely i = φ (m) (Euler's totient function: the number of integers in {1, . .., m} relatively prime to m).",
