    "text": "B–2 First solution: Suppose that P does not have n dis- tinct roots; then it has a root of multiplicity at least 2, which we may assume is x = 0 without loss of general- ity. Let xk be the greatest power of x dividing P(x), so that P(x) = xkR(x) with R(o) ≠ 0; a simple computation yields",
